!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

cloud /klaʊd/

(clouding,clouded,clouds) 

1. N-VAR A cloud is a mass of water vapour that floats in the sky. Clouds are usually white or grey in colour. 云 

例： ...the varied shapes of the clouds. …云朵的各种形状。 

例： ...a black mass of cloud. …一团乌云。 

2. N-COUNT A cloud of something such as smoke or dust is a mass of it floating in the air. (烟尘) 团 

例： The hens darted away on all sides, raising a cloud of dust. 母鸡四处飞奔，扬起一团尘土。 

3. V-T If you say that something clouds your view of a situation, you mean that it makes you unable to understand the situation or judge it properly. 蒙蔽 

例： Perhaps anger had clouded his vision, perhaps his judgment had been faulty. 也许怒火蒙蔽了他的眼睛，也许他的判断有误。 

4. V-T If you say that something clouds a situation, you mean that it makes it unpleasant. 使不快 

例： The atmosphere has already been clouded by the party's anger at the media. 该党对媒体的愤怒已经使得气氛很不愉快。 

5. V-T/V-I If glass clouds or if moisture clouds it, tiny drops of water cover the glass, making it difficult to see through. 起雾 

例： The mirror clouded beside her cheek. 紧贴她脸颊的镜子起了雾。

